  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-05 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "Synthetic adversarial UnitOfAssurance for ASME V&V 40 credibility assessment of CFD hemolysis prediction for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under VAD conditions. COU2 evaluates absolute hemolysis prediction at Model Risk Level 5 for a Class III device. The embedded weakness W-AR-05 (comparator absence/mismatch) is instantiated at defeater type D3 (undercutting via inference method mismatch): the primary validation result omits the comparedAgainst link entirely, while a secondary result references an experimental dataset collected under continuous-flow LVAD conditions at 2.5 L/min — a flow rate 40% below the minimum operating point of the declared COU (4.0–6.0 L/min). The narrative treats the lower-flow dataset as broadly applicable without examining the nonlinear shear-stress dependence of hemolysis at higher throughput, creating a plausibly deniable but materially consequential comparator mismatch.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-hemolysis-prediction-cou2",
